  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Field Marketing Assistant",
  "description": "<p>Focused on building communication skills and understanding client needs.</p><p>Responsibilities</p><ul><li><h3>Daily Work Pointers</h3><ul><li><p>Be polite, clear, and responsive in all client communications</p></li><li><p>Listen carefully to client needs and take accurate notes</p></li><li><p>Follow up promptly on requests and action items</p></li></ul><h3>Relationship-Building</h3><ul><li><p>Maintain a positive and professional attitude at all times</p></li><li><p>Support senior team members in managing client accounts</p></li><li><p>Build trust by being reliable and detail-oriented</p></li></ul><h3>Customer Service Skills</h3><ul><li><p>Learn and apply company customer service standards</p></li><li><p>Handle basic client inquiries confidently and escalate when needed</p></li><li><p>Stay calm and solution-focused when issues arise</p></li></ul><h3>Team Collaboration</h3><ul><li><p>Communicate clearly with internal teams</p></li><li><p>Share relevant client feedback with colleagues</p></li><li><p>Ask questions and learn from team members</p></li></ul><h3>Personal Development</h3><ul><li><p>Be open to feedback and continuous learning</p></li><li><p>Improve communication and time-management skills</p></li><li><p>Understand products, services, and client expectations</p></li></ul></li></ul>",
